&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Meavy Assessment Unit – B3 HCA&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;University Hospitals Plymouth NHS Trust is looking for passionate and experienced health care assistants to join our Meavy Assessment Ward as Band 3, where we are currently delivering our COVID-19 pathway and we are looking at developing the area into a 12-bedded isolation Ward for patients with transmittable diseases.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Meavy Assessment Ward is a thriving service where we aim to deliver prompt initial medical and nursing assessment and elaborate early treatment and care plans; this is all delivered thanks to the efforts of a fantastic multidisciplinary clinical team and specifically the excellent nursing team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidates will have experience in the acute setting, ideally within acute medicine, urgent care, or infectious diseases will be an asset. As a Band 3 Senior Health Care Assistant, you will support the Registered Nurses on the day-to-day management of the Ward and support the junior Health Care Assistants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return, we will support you with an innovative and individualized programme of on-going professional and career development clinical perspective – to be able to care and escalate appropriately for acutely unwell patients– and also develop your leadership skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like more information about this opportunity or to arrange an informal visit, please contact via e-mail:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Leann Sherlock, Interim Ward Manager for Meavy Ward leann.sherlock@nhs.netor Víctor Sánchez-Castrillón, Matron for Acute Medicine v.sanchez-castrillon@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;***Preference will be given to internal Trust staff, as well as ‘Priority’ and &#39;At Risk&#39; status including NHS At Risk staff throughout Devon who are able to display recent relevant experience as dictated by the Person Specification.***&lt;/p&gt;
